Easter: The Resurrection of Jesus
Easter is the most significant festival in the Christian calendar, celebrating the resurrection of Jesus Christ three days after his crucifixion. It represents victory over death and the promise of eternal life. The week leading up to Easter, known as Holy Week, includes Maundy Thursday and Good Friday. Easter Sunday is a joyful celebration with church services, flowers, and traditions like Easter egg hunts (symbolizing new life). It is the foundation of the Christian faith, signifying hope and redemption.
